52.2	Lightnin'_Hopkins	Lightnin' Hopkins	Sam John Hopkins (March 15, 1912 – January 30, 1982) better known as Lightnin’ Hopkins, was an American country blues singer, songwriter, guitarist and occasional pianist, from Houston, Texas. Rolling Stone magazine included Hopkins at number 71 on their list of the 100 greatest guitarists of all time.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/de/Lightnin_Hopkins_by_Jules_Grandgagnage.jpg/220px-Lightnin_Hopkins_by_Jules_Grandgagnage.jpg
